_refine_special_details          
;The structure exhibits pseudo-translation along the b-axis direction. 
Exact translational symmetry is broken by modulation of the tin atoms 
within the tin iodide layer and by the positions of the ammonium and 
ethylene groups of the cations, which are modulated along b. The 
smaller "basic" unit cell exhibits metrically perfect monoclinic 
C-centered symmetry, broken in the supercell. The structure also 
exhibits pseudo-inversion symmetry. Exact inversion is broken by the 
tin-iodide layer, with is ca. 95:5 disordered over pseudo-inversion 
positions (see below for details). Inversion disorder was not resolved 
for the cation portion of the structure. 

The structure was refined as a 4-component twin including pseudo-
merohedral twinning (emulating the monoclinic symmetry of the smaller 
cell, 180 degree rotation around the (0 4 1) reciprocal lattice 
direction) and inversion twinning. Application of the twin transformation 
matrix -1 0 0 0 1 0 0 0.5 -1 combined with inversion twinning resulted 
in BASF values of 0.11(2) (rotated around b-axis, not inverted), 0.43(3) 
(original domain inverted) and 0.00(2) (rotated around b-axis and 
inverted). 

The tin iodide part of the lattice was refined as disordered, with 
lead and iodide atoms approximately located in the pseudo-translated 
positions. The two moieties are related by non-crystallographic 
inversion symmetry (pseudo-inversion centers located halfway between 
major and minor moiety lead ions. The disorder emulates P-1 symmetry
if occupancy rates would be equal. ADPs of terminal iodine atoms 
related by pseudo-translation were constrained to be identical. ADPs 
of major and minor disordered iodine, tin, nitrogen and the first 
methylene C atoms were restrained to be similar (SIMU 0.01 
restraint with a distance cutoff of 4 Angstrom. The observed disorder 
necessarily creates similar disorder for the ammonium moieties of the 
cations. Positions for the minor moiety N atoms were however not 
resolved and the disorder was omitted for the cations. Subject to these 
conditions the occupancy ratio refined to 0.924(2) to 0.076(2). 

Cations are related by pseudo-translation along b with only the 
ammonium and ethylene fragments not related by exact translation, 
resulting in substantial correlation between atom positions and ADPs 
of C and S atoms. To control correlation all cations were restrained to 
have similar geometries (SAME command of Shelxl) and Uij components of 
ADPs of all C, N and S atoms closer to each other than 2.0 Angstrom were 
restrained to be similar (SIMU 0.01 command of Shelxl). For the inner 
thiophene rings all chemically equivalent bond distances were restrained 
to be either similar, or were restrained to identical target values 
(DFIX and SADI commands). The same restraints were applied to some of the 
other thiophene rings, as required for refinement stability. Necessarily 
planar segments of the cations were restrained to be flat. ADPs of sulfur 
atoms related by pseudo-translation were constrained to be identical.,Twin
;
